REGULAR.description: Conan, Kogoro, and Ran In Purple Toyota Crown GRS204 Drive pass through Mount Fuyana on their way home and are stopped by Misao Yamamura who instilled a road block in order to catch the Silver Witch, a woman who drives a White FD car and challenges people in a drag race. When the witch drifts, the tire makes a sound that sound like a woman screaming. Yamamura reveals his grandma raced against the witch but gave up when the witch drove into the air. Kogoro decides to investigate on the identity of the witch and returns to Mount Fuyana the next day, taking Conan and Ran with him in Orange Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution X (CZ4A). Upon meeting the witch, Kogoro has a drag race with her but stops when Conan reveals that the witch drove into a road less area. Kogoro tells Yamamura to stop all White FD drivers and wait for his arrival. Once there, Kogoro interrogates the three suspect pairs in order to find out which one of them is the witch.

REGULAR.description:
Sera heads to the rental villa to meet a client with Conan, Ran, and Sonoko. On their way, Ran and Sonoko spot a woman dressed in red from head to toe. At the rental villa, Tamami, Sumika, Ninda, and Hakuya, members of a former high school outdoor club, had gathered. 15 years prior, a wife stabbed her husband to death at a nearby villa.
Source: crunchyroll

Hakuya`s body is discovered, and the Nagano police led by Uehara Yoshie begin their investigation. Uehara believes the culprit struck Hakuya on the back of the head with a blunt object and knocked him unconscious before drowning him in the bathtub.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Tragedy of the Red Woman (Evil Spirit)

REGULAR.description:
Sumika is attacked by someone resembling the Red Woman, but the cut is shallow, and Uehara treats her with antiseptic. Uehara explains there was no mistake in the DNA test of the Red Woman. However, Uehera adds since over ten years ago around this time of year, rental villas in the area are robbed.
Source: crunchyroll

Comedian DoDonPa Rokusuke turns himself in at a police box for the murder of his talent agency`s president Tendo Hideki. True to his testimony, Tendo is discovered at the agency dead from a blow to the head, and DoDonPa claims he struck the president with the metal bat found beside the body.
Source: crunchyroll

REGULAR.description:
Conan feels something is wrong with DoDonPa`s all too convenient alibi and begins to strongly suspect him. After taking on the guilt for a murder he didn`t commit, DoDonPa becomes the man of the hour for trying to protect the reputation of his benefactor Tendo.
Source: crunchyroll

Author Keigo Hiura`s assistant Chiaki Minazuki is found strangled to death in a hotel. Hiura has a perfect alibi, but Conan and Sera are certain he committed the crime. They ask about the condition of Minazuki`s room and get closer to the truth. A 20 year old postcard is discovered inside Minazuki`s suitcase. It is addressed to Hiura, and the sender is not Minazuki but Jun Ota, which is also the name of the heroine in Hiura`s "The Phone, the Ocean, and I". Later a casual remark from Takagi helps Conan and Sera realize how Hiura manipulated his alibi...
Source: crunchyroll

The man who killed Head`s son is among his subordinates, and he instructs Kogoro to work with the gang as planned to determine the killer`s identity.
Source: crunchyroll

REGULAR.description:

Kogoro looks at his watch and panics when he sees the time is 2:30 in the morning. If he doesn`t determine who killed Head`s son by dawn, Ran will be killed by an assassin.
Source: crunchyroll

The Silver Detectives are the first to discover the body. While pursuing a hooligan they caught littering, they chased him into the house where they found the body. 
Source: crunchyroll

REGULAR.description:
Kogoro is hired to find the missing painter Aoki by his wife. Conan determines Aoki is in Tokugawa Prefecture`s Uozo from the painting Aoki sent his wife Midori. Kogoro, Conan, Ran, and Midori discover Aoki`s drowned corpse in Uozu. They investigate the inn where Aoki was staying and interview the manager Hayashi. When Conan sees the painting in the photo, he noticies something was added. The data from the day Aoki took the photo had been erased from his digital camera. Later, permanent part-timer Akagi, traveler Shirakawa, and fisherman Ishiguro all emerge as suspects...
Source: crunchyroll

Amuro witnesses a woman pushed from the top of the stairs at Haido Park. However, he doesn`t see the culprit`s face. The unconscious and gravely injured woman pushed from the stairs is Jodie`s friend and Haido Elementary School teacher Natsuko. Conan and Jodie head to the park and determine Natsuko was attacked somewhere else, and it soon becomes clear she was assaulted at the school. Later, Megure and the police question her coworker Sugamoto, who tried to give Natsuko a ride home, and Ueno and Kandachi, parents of students with appointments to see Natsuko...
Source: crunchyroll

Elementary school teacher Natsuko is struck while working at school and pushed off the stairs in front of the park. Conan and his companions question Sugamoto, another teacher who had planned to walk her home, and parents Ueno and Kandachi, who had appointments to meet with Natsuko. Conan notices something strange while listening to their stories. Later, the police review a photo of the answer sheets Natsuko was grading. Jodie and Camel fail to discover any information that could help them solve the crime from the photo, but Amuro and Conan realize who the culprit is after seeing the picture.
Source: crunchyroll

When Conan hears Camel`s story, he realizes Vermouth disguised herself as Jodie and spoke with him. Conan is frustrated the he acted just as Bourbon (Amuro) and Vermouth planned. Amuro meets with Vermouth, who is still disguised as Jodie. She informs him she learned from Camel that Kusuda shot himself. Amuro responds that there was another burned man who was shot in the head when Kusuda disappeared with thoughts of FBI agent Akai Shuichi on his mind. Amuro deduces Akai is still alive, but...
Source: crunchyroll

Amuro visits Okiya at the Edo family home and begins explaining how one corpse was swapped out for another. Akai was shot in the head and burned along with his car at Raiha Pass. However, Amuro believes Akai switched his own body out for Kusuda`s and is in fact still alive. Amuro explains Akai`s trick step by step to Okiya. Meanwhile, Jodie was thinking the same thing as Amuro. Amuro reasons the body swap was planned not by Akai but by Conan. Amuro then asks Okiya to remove his mask. He is certain Okiya is Akai, but...
Source: crunchyroll

Akai suddenly appears in the back seat of Jodie`s car and fires at the secret police`s vehicles. The bullet strikes a tire, and the FBI agents successfully shake off the secret police. Meanwhile, at the Kudo family home Amuro`s subordinates inform him Akai shot out a tire, causing their cars to crash. Later, Jodie`s car returns to the crash site. Akai takes a cell phone from the secret police and begins speaking to Amuro (Bourbon). He tells him it was a mistake to let Conan know he had the nickname Zero. Akai knew who Amuro truly was...
Source: crunchyroll

Sonoko`s acquaintance Chikada Eimi has her hair cut by someone at high school. Three days earlier and the day before, other students were the victims similar incidents. Before the incidents, warning letters were left in the box of Club Orihime, the romantic help desk Eimi and her friends set up at the school. This morning they received a letter stating, "EC will be brought to justice!" The letters are the initials of the victim. At the scene of the crime, they find a new letter stating, "TB dies as sundown tonight!" Only two hours remain until sunset. After finding the body of Harawaki at the shooting location of a zombie movie, Kyoko is found dead next. ゾンビが囲む別荘 (後編)

Kogoro chases a robber armed with a gun to the roof of a building. The police eventually arrest the robber, but it soon becomes clear that the robber tossed the gun while fleeing. Girls band member Hagie is murdered at a studio. Her bandmates Someka, Tadako, and Rumi are the suspects. Conan, Ran, and Sonoko arrive at the Suzuki Balloon Festival, a national hot air balloon event. During the race, reigning champion Mizuguchi Shingo`s balloon is struck by Okuda Akihiro`s and begins falling. As the balloon descends, his wife Mizuguchi Arisa falls from the balloon to her death. titles.title: Mystery in a Hot Air Balloon
ふんわり気球で怪事件

REGULAR.description:
While hiking, Kogoro, Conan, and Ran hear the moaning voice of the Tengu. After staying the night at a guest house at the bottom of the mountain, the next morning they decide to visit the Tengu`s Cave, one of the town`s historic sites. Inside the cave Conan discovers a body wearing a tengu mask hanging from the Tengu`s shrine. The body belongs to mayor Mayama. Kogoro determines the death is a suicide based on the absence of anyone else in the cave, but Conan feels there`s something off about the body and crime scene...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: You Can Hear the Tengu`s Voice

Officer worker Junko is arrested for a murder that took place in Tonkoro City. Junko confesses she was being blackmailed by the victim Katsui and killed him because she couldn`t take it anymore. However, Kogoro saw Junko in Beika City at the time of the murder. Because Tonkoro City and Beika City are an hour drive apart, Kogoro explains to Inspector Megure that it was impossible for Junko to commit the crime. Her alibi verified, Junko is released... However, a dissatisfied Conan, Kogoro, and Ran question Junko`s coworker Mayumi and her ex-boyfriend Matsubayashi as they close in on the truth.
Source: crunchyroll

A muffled sound rings down a back alleyway in the rain. When Kogoro and Conan run to the source of the sound, they find Kikuchi unconscious in the driver seat of a car parked near an intersection. In front of his car is the bleeding and dead Tsutsumi. Kikuchi is shocked when comes to and sees Tsutsumi`s body. Kikuchi and Tsutsumi were once coworkers. Kikuchi testifies that a man with an umbrella suddenly jumped into the intersection, and while he quickly slammed on the brakes, he couldn`t stop in time. Later, Tsutsumi`s will is found in his jacket pocket, and Kogoro determines it was not a traffic accident but a suicide...

titles.title: Un arrêt de bus sous la pluie

Kogoro drives Conand and Kei down a seaside highway. Six months earlier, Remi hanged herself in her apartment. Her neighbor Kei blamed herself for being unable to prevent her suicide. Turning Point on a Driving Date
ドライブデートの別れ道

Conan, Ayumi, Mitsuhiko, Genta, Ai, and Professor Agasa go to the Beika Department Store together. In the stairwell, they witness Hosokoshi, the head chef at the high-end restaurant on the top floor, being stabbed in the stomach by a disgruntled customer. Conan calls Genta, Mitsuhiko, and Ayumi to let them know the culprit escaped down a different stairway. The potential suspects are part-time worker Kamaya, housewife Mitsuko, and chef Miyanodai. Conan suddenly wakes up in the darkness. While walking with the Detective Boys to go shopping, Conan witnessed a figure breaking open a safe inside a building. Conan manages to get in touch with the Detective Boys using his badge, but he soons finds himself cornered in a desperate situation...

titles.title: Conan, piégé dans le noir, 1re partie

Conan is attacked by a theif attempting to break into a safe and trapped inside a coffin. Ai and the others realize Conan is inside Gotaro`s coffin, but the hearse is already on its way to the crematorium...

While hiking, Conan and his friends meet campers Eiko, Ashizuka, Hayashida, and Takemi at a mountain cottage. The four of them have gathered to commemorate the death of their friend Motoki who accidentally fell to their death three years ago. Takemi, who camped by herself in a tent at the bottom of a cliff, is found murdered the next morning. The time of death is estimated between 3 AM to 5 AM, making it impossible for Eiko or Ashizuka to have killed her. Suspicion falls on weather station employee Hayashida who went to a nearby mountain to collect data in the middle of the night, but something about the case bothers Conan...

Kogoro is hired by Junko to catch a thief. While working the case, the body of Junko`s neighbor Kitagami is discovered in the parking lot behind her apartment building. Kogoro reasons Kitagami got drunk and accidentally fell from his room, number 704. Inspector Megure and the police investigate the room, and Conan finds it strange that Kitagami left his front door unlocked when his apartment was fully equippped with anti-theft devices. Conan questions Sawada, the resident of 604 and room directly below Kitagami`s, and believes his death wasn`t an accident. Later, an unexpected person is revealed to be the thief, and...

Real estate company president Hiyama is murdered while holding a pair of scissors invented by Agasa, so Conan and Okiya accompany Agasa to the crime scene. The man who discovered the body is former candy shop owner Senba. Agasa suspects Senba is the murderer, but it was impossible for Senba to have entered the house with a weapon. The current case closely resembles a 17 year old case in several ways, such as the murder victim holding scissors and the sink left running at the crime scene. Conan and Okiya watch as Senba recreates the steps he took when he discovered the body and notice several contradictions...

Real estate company president Hiyama is murdered while holding a pair of scissors. The crime scene is very similar to that of an unsolved case from 17 years ago. Conan and Okiya beleive former candy shop owner Senba who discovered the body is the culprit, but are unable to determine how he brought the weapon inside the annex where the crime took place. Later, Conan and Okiya question the bodyguards standing at the entrance and identify the trick the culprit used to bring the weapon inside. They even find the weapon, and they begin solving the whole case...

titles.title: Just Like a 17 Year Old Crime Scene (Part 2)
Scènes de crime analogues à 17 ans d’intervalle (2e partie)

Kogoro agrees to conduct an interview with spirit detective Hotta and heads to a hotel with Conan for a meeting. After meeting up with Toto TV`s Kokuri, they go to Hotta`s room, but there`s no answer. As they`re standing outside the room, Kokuri notices an email he received from Hotta saying, "They`re going to kill me. Help." Around 9 AM, Kogoro and the others have a bellhop unlock the door and enter the room. Kogoro spots someone fleeing from the balcony. In the bed is Hotta`s body, stabbed numerous times in the chest...

Kogoro, Conan, and Toto TV`s Kokuri visit hotel room 402 where spirit detective Hotta Gaito is staying where they witness the fleeing suspect and discover Hotta`s murdered body. Conan examines the room while recalling the events leading up to and immediately after they opened the door. Conan and Sera have already identified the killer. Later, Conan realizes the trick the killer used based on Kogoro`s actions. Conan puts Kogoro to sleep using a tranquilizer and is about to solve the case when he realizes his bow tie-shaped voice changer is missing...

Kokubo Mamoru visits his aunt Kokubo Naoko`s home and discovers she has been murdered. While Mamoru is there, his aunt`s famously foul-mouthed myna bird Nine escapes. Naoko lives with her maid Megumi. Megumi was not at home because she was out shopping. It is revealed that Naoko, a collector of rare old books, had purchased a forgery from used book seller Sayama. Inspector Megure believes Mamoru, Megumi, or Sayama is the culprit, but all three of them have alibis. Nine says something that brings Conan closer to the truth behind the case...

Conan, Ran, Sonoko, and Okiya are invited to watch musician Hado`s rehearsal, but once they arrive, they are told by his manager Enjo that they cannot go inside. The group is shocked to learn from record company president Fuse that this will be Hado`s last concert. An argument erupts when reporter Kajiya suggests the name of Hado`s new song is also the name of his new girlfriend. Later, the fire department arrives to inspect the concert hall, where they find Hado hanging from the neck above the stage...

Musician Hado is found hanging by the neck above the stage of a concert hall. Inspector Megure believes one of Enjo, Fuse, or Kajiya committed the murder. While looking at Hado`s license and the evidence lined up at Ran`s feet, he comes to a realization. Later, Conan sees Kajiya`s footage of Hado`s face as he entered the concert hall and notices something. After confirming which objects disappeared from the crime scene, he and Amuro and Okiya search the stage and determine the truth behind the case and the trick the killer used to lift the victim`s body...

titles.title: 裏切りのステージ (後編)

Conan and his friends happen upon owner of Tamaki`s Used Bookstore, Tamaki Yujiro, and his son Ichiro having an argument. The store has become run down, and Ichiro wants his father to close it down. Later, Conan and his friends go to the park next to the bookstore, which has a genuine steam engine on display. When the steam engine`s wheels start moving at 15:00, Conan and his friends take a commemorative photo with Ichiro, who happened to be passing by. Later, they notice the shelves in the bookstore have fallen like dominos, crushing Yujiro beneath them...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Librairie ancienne et sifflet de train

A body is found brutally murdered and stabbed numerous times. The police encounter Conan and Kogoro while investigating the victim`s acquaintances. When they learn his acquaintance is located in Beika City, they decide to help the police. They arrive at investment consultant Natsukawa`s office, where they also find finance business manager Fuyuki and real estate business manager Akiba. Though they should know who may have held a grudge against victim Haruyama, the three are uncooperative...
Source: crunchyroll

A body is found brutally murdered and stabbed numerous times, and the victim`s friend Natsukawa is killed by the same method. Komoto emerges as a suspect, the man they swindled using a made-up investment opportunity ten years ago. Komoto appears before Akiba, but he accidentally falls off a cliff. The serial murders seem to be over, but the next day, Akiba is found killed by the same method. Is Komoto still alive and continuing his revenge killings...?
Source: crunchyroll

Conan, Mitsuhiko, and Genta accompany Ayumi to the park where she found a bracelet. On the road facing the park are what appear to be tire marks from a vehicle that suddenly departed as well as bloodstains. In order to return the bracelet to its owner, the Detective Boys visit various accessory shops, which eventually leads them to a certain person, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Lost Article That Smells Like a Case
Un objet trouvé à l`odeur du crime
落とし物は事件のにおい

REGULAR.description:
Officer Yamasato Futoshi, who has been assigned to a police box in Beika City starting this month, comes to the Mori Detective Agency. There was a dine and dash at a Beika City restaurant, and a similar incident occurred in Haido City where he was previously stationed. It was allegedly a blonde woman in sunglasses who looked like idol group DDPP`s Kakurai Kayoko...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 笑顔を消したアイドル

REGULAR.description:
Kobayashi-sensei, Wakasa-sensei, and the Detective Boys head to Gunma to check out the area before their class heads there for an outdoor lesson in nature. Former grade school teacher Zenda Maika is waiting for them at the train station. They get into her van and arrive at the location where they`ll be picking wild plants. They have a pleasant time at the nearby field, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: La cueillette et le trèfle (1re partie)
山菜狩りとクローバー (前編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan and the Detective Boys encounter a case while picking wild plants in the mountains. The body wasn`t in the photo they took by the car when the arrived, and the prime suspect, the victim`s own fiance Zenda Maika, has an alibi. The police discover a new suspect at the victim`s villa. Meanwhile, Conan finds the Clover Ayumi was looking for...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: La cueillette et le trèfle (2e partie)
山菜狩りとクローバー (後編)

REGULAR.description:
While Conan and Kogoro are heading to the store to go grocery shopping, they find a crowd in front of a house they`re passing by. In the middle of a badly ransacked room is a man bleeding from the head. According to the couple that lives in the house, they happened to run into the man, who was a thief. They apparently killed him when he attacked them and they fought back. It seems like a clear case of self defense, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Man Who Loved Too Much

REGULAR.description:
While walking through a residential neighborhood in Beika City, Conan and Kogoro come across a crowd of police and onlookers in front of a mansion. The mansion is the home of popular novelist Tawake Shintaro, who was found shot dead. Though there was a gun in the study where the murder took place, there are no witnesses. The body was discovered by his apprentices Akaike Naoya and Degawa Miyuki. He additionally had apprentices Bito Ryunosuke and Chigasaki Haruo for a total of four. While questioning the them, the police learn that Degawa`s apprentices wrote his books and they resented him...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Novelist Known as the Demon King
魔王と呼ばれた小説家

REGULAR.description:
The Detective Boys follow Detective Chiba after they see him purchasing a large amount of food at the convenience store. He enters an ordinary apartment building. The kids wonder if he`s come to visit a friend, but Conan explains that the building is new and deduces that Detective Chiba must be conducting a stakeout here. They follow him inside, where they find Detective Takagi as well. The Detective Boys ask to stay until the professor can come pick them up and learn that the police are staking out this building because of the jewelry store robbery that occurred the previous week.
Source: crunchyroll

While riding a monorail to the bay coast, Conan and Kogoro witness another rider being shot and injured by a sniper. The monorail makes an emergency stop, and the two of them track down the culprit, eventually arriving at the apartment believed to be the shooting location. They don`t find the culprit there, but a forensics team determines that the shot was indeed fired from that room, which is also the scene of another murder. However, the bullet extracted from the victim at the hospital is a Tokarev cartridge not suitable for sniping...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Le sniper et le monorail (1re partie)
モノレール狙撃事件 (前編)

REGULAR.description:
A passenger on the monorail Conan and Kogoro are riding is shot and injured. Their pursuit of the culprit leads them to an apartment, but the culprit they discover there has fled to Toto Market. At the market they find a bound and gagged employee. The culprit stole the employee`s possessions and is up to something...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: モノレール狙撃事件 (後編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan is invited to Agasa`s house, where learns that the professor is hoping to make a fortune selling an antique dish. Meanwhile, Haibara is anxious about Sera, who is keeping watch from in front of the house. Sera has come to check things out after being told by Ran and Sonoko that Haibara is mature for her age. Okiya shows up as well, and together they go to see the appraiser, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Antique Tray Can`t Be Hidden (Part 1)
骨董盆は隠せない (前編)

REGULAR.description:
Antique appraiser Nishitsu Hogen is stabbed to death with a spear. At the crime scene are securities company employee Tojima Motoyuki, former real estate company president Chono Kinji, and art museum director Sakamaki Suzue, all of whom came to have their black lacquer trays appraised. Professor Agasa recalls what happened when Nishitsu was still alive... Meanwhile, Sera is curious about one of Okiya`s behaviors.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Antique Tray Can`t Be Hidden (Part 2)
骨董盆は隠せない (中編)

REGULAR.description:
Appraiser Nishitsu Hogen is knocked to the ground and then stabbed to death with a spear. The police look for someone who can appraise the black lacquer trays at the crime scene but have trouble finding someone. While searching the house, the police find a box containing the dish Professor Agasa sought to have appraised. According to the housekeepers, Nishitsu said he was looking forward to seeing the surprised faces of the clients he had coming that day...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Antique Tray Can`t Be Hidden (Part 3)
骨董盆は隠せない (後編)

REGULAR.description:
A man is found bludgeoned to death at a small park in Beika City. When Conan and Kogoro pass by, they learn that the victim Mitsumoto was a scoundrel with a bad reputation and was apparently killed the previous night around 7PM. Around that same time, Hosaka, Mitsumoto`s troublemaker friend, was seen running from the park...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 悪友たちの輪舞[ロンド]

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, and Sonoko visit the Ancient Oriental Culture Museum. The objects on display are replicas at this handmade museum. Ran and Sonoko are apparently here for the Egyptian god keychains that are currently popular among high school girls. Conan looks for a way to pass the time while they`re engrossed in keychains...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and the Detective Boys are attending author Omura Kosuke`s writing class. They were introduced to him by their acquaintance Tamaki Book Cafe employee Yoshikawa Michiko. The owner of the house where the class is behind held and Omura`s sponsor book collector Nojima Ryoji and his housekeeper Takeuchi Nagisa arrive. Nojima flies into a rage after reading Genta`s novel, and...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 汽笛の聞こえる古書店3

REGULAR.description:
Ran receives a message from Ooka Momiji. It is a request for Kudo Shinichi to solve a code. A housekeeper who worked for many years at the mansion of a wealthy man passed away, leaving her four sons a code. She loved mysteries and sent each brother a different code so they would have to work together in order to find the treasure. Immediately after the brothers shared their codes with each other, they lost contact with the eldest brother. Fearing he may have encountered trouble, they put out a request for the code to be solved and find their missing brother. Momiji is coming to Kyoto on this day in order to fill them in on the details, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 大岡紅葉の挑戦状 (前編)

REGULAR.description:
At Ooka Momiji`s request, Conan and Heiji solve the code left to four sons by their mother who worked for a wealthy family for many years. They arrive at Haido Harbor Warehouse 4, where they find a man on the ground bleeding from the head and three others standing around him. They are the brothers who received the code from their mother, and the dead man is the eldest brother. They were invited to the warehouse by the eldest brother, but he was already dead by the time the first brother arrived, and the other two met up with him after that. Based on the metal frame glasses on the ground nearby, Conan and Heiji believe this was a murder...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 大岡紅葉の挑戦状 (後編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, and Kogoro come across the police investigating a crime scene. The body of a woman who was bludgeoned to death in the street the previous night was discovered. Two similar incidents occured the previous week, and the police believe all three crimes were committed by the same culprit. Because they were drunk, the victims could not recall anything about the attacks, and there are no security cameras in the area. While wandering around the crime scene, Conan spots a house. Someone is observing the crime scene from the second story...
Source: crunchyroll

Professor Agasa, Genta, Mitsuhiko, and Ayumi are eating at a third-story restaurant in the city. While looking outside from their table, through the curtains in the window, they see the silhouettes of a man and woman enjoying a party in the apartment building across from them. However, the scene shifts, and the man appears to attack the woman. The hurry to call the police, but...
Source: crunchyroll

After chatting in front of the ruined building where Western Confections Paradise plans to build its new factory, Genta, Mitsuhiko, and Ayumi discover a right hand emerging from some concrete debris. The three of them faint, and when Conan discovers them and hears what happened to them, he finds a trail of blood leading elsewhere. They believe the person whose hand they saw is alive and must have gone somewhere. They follow the trail to the Western Confections Paradise store, where they recall having a conversation a week earlier. The beautiful woman they saw then is sitting in the same seat eating the same cake now...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Ballad of the Woman Who Loved Cake
Cake o Ai Suru Onna no Ballad
ケーキを愛する女のバラード

REGULAR.description:
It`s nIghttime at the Metropolitan Police Academy. As the cherry blossoms fall, the sounds of Furuya Rei and Matsuda Jinpei duking it out echo across the premises. Even though they`re attending a police academy, Matsuda dislikes Furuya`s determination to become a police officer no matter what. Neither one gives any ground as their fight continues. Around 2AM, Morofushi Hiromitsu wakes from a nightmare and hears a knock on his door. Standing outside his room is Furuya, who is covered in injuries. Upon seeing him, Morofushi asks Furuya if he thinks he`ll get along with the guy who did that to him. During their morning assembly, standing next to the injured Furuya and Matsuda are their classmates Morofushi Hiromitsu, Hagiwara Kenji, and Date Wataru. Rookie class instructor Onizuka Hachizo asks how they got their injuries, but Date thinks quickly and tells him a lie. Furuya finds it odd when Matsuda demonstrates a thorough understanding of a police officer`s responsibilities despite his hatred of the police and begins investigating his past.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Keisatsu Gakkou Hen: Wild Police Story - Case. Matsuda Jinpei
Police Academy Arc: Wild Police Story - Case. Matsuda Jinpei
警察学校編 Wild Police Story CASE.松田陣平

REGULAR.description:
While walking through a residential neighborhood in Koneru after finishing a job, Kogoro hears a scream. He follows the scream and finds a man named Esaka Ritsuo sitting on the ground. Apparently someone pushed his back while he was waiting for the signal to change and was nearly hit by a car. At the detective agency, Conan and Kogoro listen to Esaka`s story. He has lost his memories from the past year and believes he may have done something to incur someone`s enmity during that time...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and Kogoro conduct an investigation in Koneru in order to find the lost memories of Esaka Ritsuo, who lived in the area for the past year. In Koneru, he`s reunited with the people he spent time with, and he nearly regains his memories when he`s barked at by a dog. Two days later, Conan and Kogoro head to Esaka`s home with high hopes, where they learn he`s been found dead.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and Ran are at the studio of Kasuga Ryuji the artist. Kasuga approached Ran in front of a department store while she was out shopping, and she has been working part time as his model. Kasuga`s assistant Rokui Riko and his apprentice Komiyama Yoshio are at the studio as well. When Conan sees something shining unnaturally outside the window, he goes into the yard to investigate, where he learns something from the gardener...
Source: crunchyroll

While the Detective Boys excitedly discuss soccer on the way home from school, Conan is thinking about a different news story. Missing professional shogi player Nishikido, who was suspected of matching fixing, was murdered and found dead. At the crime scene was a shogi board with one leg cut off. The kids are discussing the origin of the term "yaocho" (match fixing) featured in the article Conan was reading when Haneda Shukichi shows up. Shukichi explains that he played against Nishikido and describes his impression of the man. The Detective Boys notice Shukichi is neatly dressed and believe he`s going on a date with his girlfriend Yumi, but Shukichi denies it, saying he`s meeting someone important instead, and leaves. Soon afterwards, Yumi shows up following Shukichi, as she finds his behavior suspicious. Claiming he`s less likely to notice she`s following him if she has a child with her, Yumi drags Conan off with her. Conan and Yumi follow Shukichi and witness him buying a bunch of donuts and having a friendly conversation with a couple of women...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Le plateau de shôgi de Taikô Meijin (1er coup)
太閤名人の将棋盤 (初手編)

REGULAR.description:
At the apartment where Shukichi attends shogi study sessions, one of its members Genda Yasukiyo is murdered. The home of former study group member Kishida Yuhei catches fire, and his body is found inside. Meanwhile, Shukichi appears to have noticed something related to the identity of the culprit and is kidnapped. Conan meets up with Akai, and together they go to rescue Shukichi.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 太閤名人の将棋盤 (妙手編)

REGULAR.description:
At the apartment where Shukichi attends shogi study sessions, Genda Yasukiyo, one of the group`s members, is murdered. The home of former study group member Kishimoto Yuhei catches fire, and his body is found inside. Meanwhile, Shukichi seems to have noticed a clue to the culprit`s identity and is kidnapped. Conan meets up with Akai, and together they go to rescue Shukichi.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 太閤名人の将棋盤 (王手編)

REGULAR.description:
Professor Agasa brings Conan, Ayumi, Mitsuhiko, and Genta to a snowy mountain in the winter to go skiing. On their way to the ski resort, they meet drug manufacturing company president Ishibashi Kengo and doctor Yokoyama Takeru when they discover their car stuck in the snow and help them get unstuck. Apparently they are on their way to go sport hunting. They part ways after exchanging contact information, but a suspicious car follows along after them...
Source: crunchyroll

Ayumi witnesses medicine manufacturing company president Ishibashi Kengo murdering Dr. Yokoyama Takeru at a ski resort. Ishibashi realizes what happened, and he attempts to chase down Conan, Ayumi, Mitsuhiko, and Genta. As they are fleeing from him, they end up off the ski trail and must walk through the snow, where they encounter two of Ishibashi`s goons waiting for them. Though they use their sled to escape their pursuers, the goons meet up with Ishibashi and resume their search for the Detective Boys. The kids end up at a cabin. As Conan is using his phone in an attempt to make contact with the outside world, he manages to get in touch with Professor Agasa, but...
Source: crunchyroll

Furuya and Date fight one another during their arresting techniques class. When Date wins, he asks Furuya why he didn`t go after his weak point and that he must be stronger than anyone else if he wants to carry out justice. That night, Furuya contemplates Date`s words while lying in bed alone. Morofushi arrives at Furuya`s room to inform him he`s going out. Furuya says he doesn`t need anything when Morofushi asks but remembers shortly afterwards that he`s out of toothpaste. He exits his room to ask Morofushi, Hagiwara, and Matsuda to pick some up, but they`re already gone, so Furuya heads to the convenience store alone. He finds Date outside, who tells him about a past incident with his father...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Keisatsu Gakkou Hen: Wild Police Story - Case. Date Wataru
Police Academy Arc: Wild Police Story - Case. Date Wataru
警察学校編 Wild Police Story CASE.伊達航

REGULAR.description:
Conan arrives at Cafe Poirot because Ran and Kogoro are going out, where he finds store employee Azusa making jack-o`-lanterns for Halloween. While helping her, Conan learns everyone is talking about the recent discovery of some jack-o`-lantern ghosts. Just then, three men and women hurry into the store, claiming their pumpkins have been stolen...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 空飛ぶハロウィンカボチャ

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ayumi, Mitsuhiko, and Genta go out for a drive in Professor Agasa`s car. On their way home, they pass a building with an unnaturally flickering light in a third-story office. Deciphering the Morse code for SOS, they head to the office, where they find a tied up motorcycle deliveryman. He claims a bomb has been planted in the room, and the hurriedly flee the scene.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Case of Ayumi`s Illustrated Diary 2

REGULAR.description:
An old woman is pushed down the stone steps of a temple in Beika City. She claims she was pushed by a young woman, but there is no other information about the case. In the crowd is a man staring at the old woman. The police speak with him, but he suspiciously claims he doesn`t know anything about the incident and leaves. He seems to have witnessed what happened, but for some reason he can`t speak about it...
Source: crunchyroll

Hagiwara, Furuya, Date, and Morofushi spot an RX-7FD3S at the police academy. It`s apparently Hagiwara`s favorite model, and he overwhelms Instructor Onizuka with an impassioned speech when the instructor exits the car. However, the car belongs not to Onizuka but a senior cop who died on duty. The deceased cop`s daughter wants to become a police officer, and Onizuka is holding onto the car until then. Later, during heavy equipment training, they discuss Hagiwara`s earlier behavior. Hagiwara knows a lot about cars because his family ran an auto repair shop. However, his family`s shop was forced to close, and he explains that he`s trying to become a police officer because the police force will never go bankrupt. After training, a man approaches Hagiwara and Matsuda...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Keisatsu Gakkou Hen: Wild Police Story - Case. Hagiwara Kenji
Police Academy Arc Wild Police Story CASE. Hagiwara Kenji
警察学校編 Wild Police Story CASE.萩原研二

REGULAR.description:
The Detective Boys arrive at the apartment of Mitsuhiko`s acquaintance. He creates figures with the members of his university club and has agreed to show his club`s figures to the kids. The kids are shown around the studio, but one of the club members is unhappy about it from start to finish. His mood is apparently related to the contest to which they`re planning to submit the figure they`re currently working on...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and Kogoro see a patrol car parked in front of the apartment building they happen to pass by. Inside the building, a woman who lives alone was found dead. Three sets of fingerprints were found at the crime scene. The first set belongs to the man she was dating, and the second set belongs to the owner of the bar she worked at. The police have no record of the final set. Since there are no signs of forced entry, the police believe she was killed by an acquaintance.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan, Ran, Sonoko, and Sera are invited to their classmate Sekizawa Yumi`s birthday party. Because her older sister Sekizawa Remi the model`s birthday is one day earlier, their joint birthday party is attended by numerous celebrities, Remi`s manager Kushiyama Mitomu, Remi`s classmate and pastry chef Hatsune Tsuguo, and hair and makeup artist Hanasaki Mizutoshi. Conan, who has trouble speaking due to the cold sore he developed several days earlier, takes out a pill case so he can take some medicine before the party starts when he`s spotted by Sera. Inside the case is the APTX-4869 antidote Haibara gave him during his school trip...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Birthday Party of Divine Punishment (Part 1)
天罰くだる誕生パーティー (前編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, Sonoko, and Sera attend the birthday party of their classmate Sekizawa Yumi and her older sister and model Sekizawa Remi. During the party, while the restaurant lights have been turned off for a slideshow, hair and makeup artist Hanasaki Mizutoshi, who had been hitting on the Sekizawa sisters, can be heard groaning in pain. When the lights come on, Hanasaki`s dead body is on the floor. Furthermore, the words "divine punishment" have been written on his forehead... Meanwhile, Sera recalls the day her mother Mary was turned into a child.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Birthday Party of Divine Punishment (Part 2)
天罰くだる誕生パーティー (後編)

REGULAR.description:
A man arrives at the Mori Detective Agency claiming his girlfriend has been kidnapped by a red sheep. The man received a threatening message, but for some reason, there was no demand for a ransom. Upon seeing the sheep, Conan and Ran feel like they once saw the same sheep a long time ago. Kogoro and the client head to the park at night, but... Meanwhile, curious about the red sheep, Conan and Ran head to the park as well.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Akai Hitsuji no Bukimi na Game (Zenpen)
赤いヒツジの不気味なゲーム (前編)

REGULAR.description:
While Kogoro is investigating the false kidnapping of the Red Sheep game meant to test a boyfriend`s courage and love, Conan and Ran run into someone wearing a red sheep costume in the street at night. After the red sheep departs, they find the body of restaurant La Mucho owner and head cook Wakabayashi Tetsusaburo. Because the restaurant is also the workplace of Takigawa Ami, who set up the false kidnapping, and her boyfriend Beppu Ryota, they believe the incidents are related and visit the restaurant. While asking about alibis, they learn that since several weeks ago, videos featuring a red sheep pranking couples and running away have been getting a lot of attention on a video sharing site. Meanwhile, the police searching Wakabayashi`s home discover a threatening message on his computer...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Akai Hitsuji no Bukimi na Game (Kouhen)
赤いヒツジの不気味なゲーム (後編)

REGULAR.description:
The body of a man is discovered at an abandoned construction site within the metropolitan area. Brought to the scene by an anonymous call, judging by the condition of the body, the police believe the murder took place elsewhere. Meanwhile, unable to get in touch with the man`s family, a local police officer is sent to the victim`s home. The safe within the ransacked home has been left open, and an ornament with blood and hair stuck to it is found on the floor. After examining the scene, the police determine the crime took place here and begin their investigation. Two days later, the police identify a man who persistently hounded the victim. Inspector Megure is shocked when he hears his name. It is a man with a grudge against him due to something that happened three years earlier. Inspector Megure risks his own career to arrest him, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Threat to Megure`s Police Career
目暮, 刑事人生の危機

REGULAR.description:
Conan and Ran accompany Kogoro to the mansion of a client, soft-serve ice cream maker Morikawa Yuzan. Yuzan has cancer and not long left to live, and asks Kogoro to advise him on distributing his legacy. At the mansion are his heirs and sons Moriakwa Yuichiro, Morikawa Yujiro, and Morikawa Yuzaburo, as well as Oi Hiroki the lawyer and Shito Yuka the chief butler. The brothers won`t stop talking about the inheritance, and each one is desperate to get his hands on their father`s legacy...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and Ran accompany Kogoro to the mansion of a client, soft-serve ice cream maker Morikawa Yuzan. Yuzan has cancer and not long left to live and asks Kogoro to evaluate his three potential heirs. His third son Morikawa Yuzaburo is found dead inside a locked room. Furthermore, his second son Morikawa Yujiro, who had been missing since the previous day, is found dead inside the soft serve tank. His eldest son Morikawa Yuichiro breaks down, saying he`s next, and locks himself inside his room.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and the Detective Boys are hanging out at Professor Agasa`s house watching "Softie Sadao and Scaredy-cat Toshiko Visit Haunted Locations" paranormal videos on a streaming site. Conan and Haibara accompany the other three to an abandoned hospital so they can film their own ghost video at a haunted location. They begin filming as they head towards the locked room on the third floor said to be inhabited by a ghost. Apparently there are a variety of spooky rumors regarding this location...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Detective Boys` Test of Courage

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ayumi, Mitsuhiko, Genta, and Haibara are on the bus with Kobayashi-sensei and Wakasa-sensei to Hatoyama Ranch to collect the new chickens they`ll be caring for at school. Also on the bus are Hitsuka Junya, Nanbu Takashi, and Kano Shogo, who are headed to the same ranch. They are apparently going there to gather information and conduct research. There`s trouble on the bus, but Amuro saves the day. Amuro seems to have business at the ranch as well...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Spark That Fell on the Ranch (Part 1)
牧場に墜ちた火種 (前編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan and his companions head to a ranch to pick up some chickens for their grade school and get dragged into a dangerous situation. A man claiming to be the ranch owner`s younger brother takes Ayumi hostage and locks Conan, Amuro, Mitsuhiko, and Kobayashi in the basement beneath the office. There they find the body of the ranch owner and Kazami Yuya. Conan successfully gets in touch with Haibara and the others above ground, but... What are the objectives of the three men visiting the ranch and the owner`s younger brother?
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Spark That Fell on the Ranch (Part 2)
牧場に墜ちた火種 (後編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan and Kogoro meet a manager of an accounting firm at the hospital who`s been told he has six months left to live. Also with him are his wife and secretary, and it seems as though he plans to make the most of his remaining time. However, several days later, he`s found murdered in his home. That morning, his wife and secretary went out to run an errand at his request. When they returned that evening, they found him dead in the bathroom. Just then, the man`s friend comes running in.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and Kogoro see a news story on TV about the disappearance of traffic accident victim Butsumaru Daijiro. Mori Fusae, the woman who witnessed the accident, handed over Butsumaru`s driver`s license to the police, but Inukai Hajime, the man who caused the accident, vanished after saying he would take Butsumaru to the hospital. Meanwhile, the Mori Detective Agency receives a phone call from Butsumaru`s wife Emiko, who hires Kogoro to find her husband and bring him back safe...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: あの人を取り戻したい

REGULAR.description:
Conan hears two women scream while on the way to the park with Genta and Mitsuhiko. They go to the house where they heard the screams, where they see Hirasawa Kaori and Hirasawa Seiko, who have fallen down some stairs. From their conversation with Hirasawa Ryoji, who arrives shortly afterwards, they learn the women are his wife and mother-in-law, and he is the family`s son-in-law. It seems as though all they do is cause trouble for Ryoji. Later, Conan and his friends see Ryoji struggling near the park. According to Ayumi, her neighbors have been talking about the Hirasawa family...
Source: crunchyroll

Kogoro spots Inspector Megure walking in front of Cafe Poirot. He congratulates the police on recently solving a case in record time, but apparently they arrested the wrong man. Conan meets up with them and Inspector Megure explains the case to them. A man was found dead in his home. At the crime scene were a rope and metal pipe, and the police believe the culprit entered by opening a hole in a glass window, knocked the victim unconscious with the metal pipe, and then strangled him to death. The victim`s girlfriend`s testimony pointed to her ex-boyfriend as a possible suspect, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Man Who Camped Out at the Police Station

REGULAR.description:
Okino Yoko comes to the Mori Detective Agency to ask him to solve a murder that happened at a villa. Several days earlier, Yoko headed to a villa where a Nichiuri TV producer`s sister went missing after she got married to scout the location. His sister`s husband and brother- and sister-in-law were there as well. But the night they decided to stay at the villa... Just as he was preparing to explain his deduction, Kogoro shuts himself inside the bathroom instead. Wakita Kanenori from Iroha Sushi shows up at the office, and then--?!
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Okino Yoko and the Locked Attic (Part 1)
Okino Youko to Yaneura no Misshitsu (Zenpen)
沖野ヨーコと屋根裏の密室 (前編)

REGULAR.description:
Okino Yoko comes to the detective agency, and Wakita Kanenori and Conan end up having to solve the case she describes that happened at a certain villa. The people present at the villa during the case had all kinds of relationships with the woman who went missing two years ago, giving all of them possible motives for killing the murder victim in the case. While attempting to solve the case based on things Yoko found strange, Conan receives a message from Kogoro, who is in the bathroom...?
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Okino Yoko and the Locked Attic (Part 2)
Okino Youko to Yaneura no Misshitsu (Kouhen)
沖野ヨーコと屋根裏の密室 (後編)

REGULAR.description:
While Instructor Onizuka is reprimanding his police cadets, Morofushi spots the missing person report for a young girl who went missing the previous night. His friends ask him why he`s so interested in the girl, but simply explains that she looks similar to a girl he used to play with as a child and refuses to elaborate. With coaxing from his friends, Morofushi eventually opens up and begins telling them about the murders he witnessed as a child...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Keisatsu Gakkou Hen: Wild Police Story - Case. Morofushi Hiromitsu
Police Academy Arc Wild Police Story Case. Morofushi Hiromitsu
警察学校編 Wild Police Story CASE. 諸伏景光

REGULAR.description:
The Detective Boys discover an abandoned car by the river. Though they`re interested in the car, they quickly head off to play because rain is forecasted for that evening. While playing soccer, Genta nearly runs into a nearby woman. She was speaking into a voice recorder, but their near collision leads to her playing soccer with the kids. After a while, they begin hearing thunder, so they leave behind the woman who seems to be waiting for someone. The next morning, Conan sees a certain story on the news...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Spiral of Rain and Malice
雨と悪意のスパイラル

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, and Kogoro arrive at a chicken egg factory. Kogoro is asked to investigate what`s causing the strange things that have been happening to chicken sexer Nanba over the past few weeks and act as his bodyguard. They question the factory employees, but nobody can think of anyone who would want to harm him. However, one of his colleagues seems to have reservations about him. Furthermore, they learn about a chicken sexing legend from the reporter who has come to the factory to gather information. Later, when they attend Nanba`s lecture, they witness an attack on him...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 狙われたひよこ鑑定士

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, and Sonoko have come to the newest date spot. When they discover the elderly Kamogawa Haru anxiously sitting on a bench, they go to speak to her believing she may be lost. Just then, a man appears. Conan and his friends assume he is Haru`s son based on his appearance, but he is apparently her boyfriend Kazama Joji. Noticing that Haru is fairly wealthy, Sonoko believes Kazama, who is young enough to be Haru`s son, is a gold-digger and cautions her against the relationship, but the couple blows her off...
Source: Crunchyroll

titles.title: The Dreamy-Eyed Woman`s Last Shot at Love
夢見る貴婦人, 最後の恋

REGULAR.description:
A woman named Nishiwaki Kae arrives at the Mori Detective Agency where Conan and Kogoro are. She explains that someone has been breaking into her apartment while she`s at work and asks Kogoro for help. The intruder, who began breaking in a month ago, apparently is not a thief, but leaves gifts for her. The three of them head to her apartment and discover a suitcase with a ribbon on it in the entryway. Believing it is a new gift from the intruder, Kogoro opens the suitcase and finds a dead body packed inside...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and Kogoro are attending a wedding. Kogoro met the groom`s father at a bar where he`s a regular and ended up receiving an invitation. Also attending the wedding are staff including the wedding planner and priest, as well as the couple`s friends. The ceremony begins, and just as the bride enters the chapel, she begins choking and loses consciousness. Upon seeing her pain, the people in attendance say ominous things such as "she got what she deserved" and "this wedding was cursed."
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Shi ga Futari o Wakatsu made
死が二人を分かつまで

REGULAR.description:
Conan and Kogoro pass by a dreary shopping center. They attempt to purchase some things at a vegetable shop, but the owner, Yamazaki, seems listless. Just then, Madam Gaga, a producer who revitalizes run down shopping centers, and her assistant Rabbit Suzuki show up. Madam Gaga announces that a pro wrestling event will be held to revitalize the shopping center. The shop owners engage in various forms of exercise to train, and Kogoro agrees to participate in the event as a referee, but...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan, Haibara, Ayumi, Genta, and Mitsuhiko arrive at a takeout pizza restaurant. They participate in the store`s campaign to guess the weight of a ball of pizza dough, and thanks to Genta, they win a free pizza. After splitting the pizza into fifths and placing their slices inside special boxes, they head home. On their way, all of them have their pizza stolen by someone. When the kids meet back up, each one has a torn pizza box. Conan and Mitsuhiko realize based on the damage that the culprit was after their boxes.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 円谷光彦の探偵ノート

REGULAR.description:
The Mori Detective Agency receives a phone call from client Nagamine Mayako. Mayako has an appointment at the agency office, but she seems to have gotten lost. Though it`s past her scheduled appointment time, Kogoro, who knows from her social media photos that Mayako is beautiful, seems excited. The client noticed her husband has been acting suspiciously and would like him to investigate the possibility that he is involved in criminal activity. Kogoro continues waiting for a while, but Mayako never shows up, and the agency receives another phone call...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Sweet Voice Heard Through the Phone
受話器ごしのスウィートボイス

REGULAR.description:
While on their way home from visiting Professor Agasa`s friend`s apartment, Conan, Ayumi, Mitsuhiko, and Genta hear a scream. They rush to the scene, where they discover a man bleeding from the head as well as a woman. The woman who lives at the apartment noticed something off about the place when she came home and grabbed the golf club she kept for self-defense. The lights wouldn`t turn on, and as she entered the apartment, she heard a loud noise... The police confirm her story and believe it was an unfortunate accident. However, certain elements of the case catch Conan`s attention...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Surprise That Leads to Tragedy
サプライズは悲劇のはじまり

REGULAR.description:
Yusaku is approached by a TV reporter when he exits the Metropolitan Police Department. He`s asked if he visited the police to confirm that the false charges against Kaito Kid had been dropped. However, Yusaku responds that his assistance was requested with the series of locked room murders that recently took place. He announces that he has solved the cases and will reveal the solution on a live broadcast over the weekend and even leaves a message for Kid before he departs. However, Yusaku runs into trouble on the day of the broadcast!
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 工藤優作の推理ショー (前編)

REGULAR.description:
Three victims who seem to share nothing in common are discovered within locked rooms in the serial locked room murder case. Yusaku`s advice was requested by the Metropolitan Police Department, and he was scheduled to solve the case on live TV, but he ends up sick in bed with food poisoning. Yukiko, who was going to disguise herself as him and appear in his place, gets sick as well. Conan hears the doorbell ring and goes to open the door to the Kudo family home to turn down the TV appearance but comes face to face with Yusaku, who should be sick in bed...?! Kudo Yusaku`s unrehearsed and unprepared detective show begins!
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 工藤優作の推理ショー (後編)

REGULAR.description:
Ayumi runs into a purse-snatcher and the man pursuing them, Kume Shosaku. The other Detective Boys arrive, and while they`re being filled in, a body is discovered in the apartment complex the culprit fled into. Next to the body are the jacket the culprit was wearing and the bag they stole. However, the money is missing from inside the bag, and the dead man doesn`t look like the culprit. Meanwhile, Inspector Megure receives a call that the body of a man who has Kume`s wallet and 300,000 yen has been discovered.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Detective Boys` Pursuit of the Purse-snatcher
探偵団の引ったくり大追跡

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, and Kogoro are invited to visit Shimonoseki by the lawyer Oi, who they previously met during the inheritance dispute case. The clients are the fourth generation owner Izumiya Makoto and his daughter Kaede, who run the long-established fugu restaurant Izumiya. A thief entered their house while the restaurant was busiest and no one was home and stole their family`s treasured cooking pot. While the pot is valuable, to the family, its true worth is in the broth that`s seeped into the pot since the restaurant`s founding. Conan and his companions question the four suspects identified by Oi`s investigation, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Tecchiri Taiketsu Mystery Tour (Mojikou Kokura Hen)
The Boiled Fugu Mystery Tour Showdown (Mojiko & Kura Part)
てっちり対決ミステリーツアー (門司港・小倉編)

REGULAR.description:
The lawyer Oi sends Conan, Ran, and Kogoro are sent to Izumiya, a long-established fugu restaurant in Shimonoseki, and are hired to find the family`s stolen treasured cooking pot. During their investigation, Kogoro comes into contact with a suspicious person in the city at night. Once he`s alone, they tell him to mind his own business and attack him. Is his attacker one of the four suspects they questioned during their investigation? Conan visits their restaurants to speak with them again and taste the dishes they pride themselves on.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Boiled Fugu Mystery Tour Showdown (Shimonoseki Part)
てっちり対決ミステリーツアー (下関編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan and Kogoro discover a body in a busy downtown area. The victim died instantly when he was struck on the head with a metal pipe, and there`s a dying message in the street. They visit the victim`s apartment, where the property manager tells them he said he`d pay all the rent he owed as early as the next day. The Utagawa Corporation CEO enters the picture when the manager describes how the victim reacted to the magazine he was reading the day of the murder, introducing the possibility that the victim was killed for attempting to blackmail the CEO...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: カリスマ社長の極秘計画

REGULAR.description:
For several days, pairs of unidentified foreigners have been turning up dead. While discussing the case on their way home from school, Conan, Genta, Mitsuhiko, Ayumi, and Haibara come across a foreigner who has fallen off a building. When Conan sees Vodka on the roof, he instructs Haibara to take the three kids and leave the scene. Conan discovers an FBI ID and phone displaying a coded message on the fallen foreigner and heads to the Kudo family home, where he finds a gathering of FBI agents.
Source: crunchyroll

For several days, the Black Organization has been killing FBI agents. Conan and the FBI deduce that the Organization must be deciphering the FBI`s coded messages, so they decide to use it against them by laying a trap for them. Supposedly dead Camel and Mark, the older brother of a killed agent, are chosen to go to the meeting location. However, no one arrives at the location indicated by the code, and shots are fired on the agents keeping watch. Will Camel be able to evade the Black Organization without them realizing he`s still alive?!
Source: crunchyroll

Cornered by the Black Organization the FBI were trying to trap, Camel drives his car into the ocean. He manages to escape to Umizaru Island, where he warms up at the campsite. However, his location is given away when they spot his fire. The Black Organization arrives on the island in order to kill Camel and get a look at his face. In order to evade them, Camel acquires coffee bean bags and straws from the cafe on the island as instructed by Akai, but... How will the Black Organization`s battle against the FBI over Agent Camel end?!
Source: crunchyroll

Ayumi, Genta, and Mitsuhiko invite Conan and Haibara to the Beika department store. They have their sights set on the department store lottery`s grand prize, a Hachijo-jima whale watching tour. The professor asks Haibara to withdraw some cash for him, so she heads to the bank`s ATM. However, Kogoro arrived just before her, and his card has been swallowed by the machine. On their way to another branch, they spot a suspicious man in a black coat. He appears shocked when he sees Haibara, and then...
Source: crunchyroll

While playing at the park, Conan, Genta, Mitsuhiko, Ayumi, and Haibara hear a dog barking loudly and a woman screaming. They head to the location of the sound, where they find housewife Yamada Sachiko and her beloved dog Pan being attacked by a man wearing a ski mask. Rather than rescuing his owner, Pan flees during the commotion. With help from Conan and the kids, Sachiko escapes danger. Sachiko, who doesn`t know why she was attacked, heads home with Pan once he returns, but Conan and the kids are curious about the masked man`s goals and decide to investigate.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: My Beloved Dog Pan-kun Is a Good Boy
愛犬パン君はおりこうさん

REGULAR.description:
Conan and Kogoro are enjoying a meal at an Italian bar in an alley while chatting with the owner Yamaura when the wall is suddenly demolished. The culprit is Kusumi, the owner of the alley, who has been harassing shop owners who refuse to vacate the alley. One shop owner even died from the stress. Sushi restaurant owner Fumio and creative cuisine restaurant owner Yonezawa arrive when they hear the commotion, and with their help, they successfully run off Kusumi. But when Kogoro visits the bathroom a while later, he discovers someone inside...
Source: crunchyroll

Kawasaki Frontale takes on FC Tokyo in the J League 30th anniversary match. Conan and the Detective Boys have fun participating in the special event. However, once the event ends and they return to their seats, for some reason Haibara is in a bad mood. She wanted to enter the pitch holding hands with her favorite player Higo of Big Osaka, but she showed up on the wrong day. Haibara expresses her disappointment over her team`s loss and Sanada`s poor play... only to realize Sanada is standing right next to her! While watching the match together, Haibara notices something odd in the stands.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Behind the Scenes of the J League Finals

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, and Kogoro encounter some men arguing at the hospital. They are Ryoichi and Reiji, the sons of Kenzo, president of Aizawa foods, and senior executive director Bando. Kenzo, who is inside the treatment room, is the cause of their argument. The three men begin telling Kogoro about the circumstances when Kenzo collapsed in the refrigerated warehouse when the doctor finishes treating Kenzo. Kenzo, who is now awake, tells the others that he simply fell asleep from exhaustion. However, Conan senses there is something off about Kenzo`s words and behavior.
Source: crunchyroll

Kazuha is visiting Tokyo, and Conan and Ran join her on a trip to Haido Shrine, which is said to provide matchmaking benefits. Because today is a lucky day, the shrine grounds are crowded with people. Ran, who wasn`t aware the shrine was a popular spot, asks Kazuha how she learned about it. She apparently learned about the shrine through Heiji when she happened to see him looking it up on his phone. Based on his recent behavior, Conan realizes Heiji must be here as well and goes after the suspicious man wearing a fox man he spots. Meanwhile, Kazuha notices someone in the crowd who doesn`t seem interested in matchmaking...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and Ran are invited to Haido Shrine by Kazuha, where they meet Heiji wearing a fox mask. The four of them get caught up in the murder that takes place there. The victim is Hidaka, an investigative police officer, who was looking at flashcards of mugshots of wanted criminals. Believing Hidaka was pursuing wanted criminals at the shrine, Conan and Heiji contact Detective Takagi, who finds three wanted criminals among the shrine visitors. Each criminal has a reason for remaining at the shrine and seems to have been aware of Hidaka`s presence...
Source: crunchyroll

While on their way to go shopping, Conan and the Detective Boys hear a man scream. They head towards the sound, which brings them to a tanning salon. Inside the building is salon employee Tsunoda Yasuo, who informs them that there is a dead body in the third room from the back. They head down the dark hallway and find the body of Nishitani Shin inside a tanning machine. He is a bodybuilder with tanning gel rubbed all over his body in order to achieve an even tan. The police arrive, and according to their investigation, the gel was poisoned...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Case of Ayumi`s Illustrated Diary 3

REGULAR.description:
While passing by Doterasu Shrine in Beika City, the Detective Boys hear a scream and rush to the scene. They find Jupita on the ground, who struck his head after falling down the stone steps. Jupita is taken to the hospital and is likely to survive.  Jupita`s older sister and rising songwriter Juria and her mentor Saimon meet the Detective Boys at the hospital. Just before being attacked by a mugger, Jupita called Juria to tell her he was in another town. The Detective Boys begin investigating why Jupita lied about coming to Beika City.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and the Detective Boys arrive at a candy shop that`s just reopened. A band is playing, and the kids are given plums to celebrate the grand opening. Ayumi, Mitsuhiko, and Genta are fascinated by their first traditional candy, but Conan doesn`t seem interested. Genta calls Conan arrogant for acting all grown up. The two get into an argument, and Conan leaves alone. On his way home, an old man jumps out of an alleyway, declares he`s seen an omurice corpse, and requests Conan`s help...!
Source: crunchyroll

While walking down a deserted road after completing a job, Conan, Ran, and Kogoro hear the sound of an alarm whistle and a scream. The sound leads them to security guard Nezu Goro, who has been stabbed in the stomach with a knife. Nezu points towards the main avenue and says the words "white clothes" before he dies. Furthermore, at the top of the stairs Nezu is thought to have fallen down is the crying and screaming Yuki Keiko and the body of her husband Yuki Hideto, the IT company president. Conan heads towards the main avenue in pursuit of the culprit where he encounters a young man dressed in black.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Culprit Who Disappeared into the Sleeping Town
眠れる街に消えた犯人

REGULAR.description:
Even as the band rushes around to get ready, the day of their first live performance is upon them. None of them feel ready, but before they know it, it`s time to go on. As Tomori stands on the stage, her legs trembling, the crowd grows restless.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and the Detective Boys discover Detectives Takagi and Chiba on a stakeout. Believing the children will leave once they realize there`s nothing for them to do, they begin explaining the robbery that occurred that morning. The culprit has been identified as unemployed man Fujiki Kazuma, but he hasn`t returned home. The police`s investigation turned up Fujiki`s ex-girlfriend, who he is likely to turn to for help if he`s on the run. Though the children are told the culprit has been identified and there`s no mystery to solve, something catches Conan`s attention...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan, Haibara, Ayumi, Genta, and Mitsuhiko visit Teitan Elementary School to take care of the rabbits. The man they encounter there sees Haibara and asks if she`s Miyano Akemi`s younger sister Shiho. His question frightens Haibara, but he is Teitan Elementary School graduate Murata Sho. His former classmates Yanagimachi Gaku and Ichihashi Seiko join him, and Conan and the Detective Boys learn Akemi attended Teitan Elementary School. The graduates planned to dig up the time capsule they buried when they graduated, but only Akemi knew where it was buried...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 宮野明美のタイムカプセル (前編)

REGULAR.description:
While taking care of the rabbits at the animal shed, Conan, Haibara, Ayumi, Genta, and Mitsuhiko meet Teitan Elementary School graduates Murata Sho, Yanagimachi Gaku, and Ichihashi Seiko. They`ve been asked to dig up a time capsule while the rest of their class prepares for the class reunion. Akemi, the only person who knows the location of the buried time capsule, left behind a code, and the Detective Boys work with the graduates to find clues. But something strange happens during the search, and Conan believes someone may be interfering with their search for the time capsule.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 宮野明美のタイムカプセル (後編)

REGULAR.description:
Nakajima Takako visits the Mori Detective Agency and explains that her husband is missing. She lost contact with him three days ago, and the police aren`t taking her concerns seriously. Conan and Kogoro begin examining the husband`s personal effects they received from Takako. Among his belongings are photos from their honeymoon, of her husband diving with his coworker and a ship`s captain, and her husband posing with his younger brother in front of their parents` home. They find nothing remarkable on the husband`s computer, so they visit his workplace, but...
Source: crunchyroll

As Conan, Ayumi, Genta, Mitsuhiko, and Haibara finish helping park warden Kimishima Satoshi, he asks them to find the owner of a lost baseball cap. They follow the clues to the home of Katsumi Nozomu, where they find a police officer patrolling the neighborhood and warning Katsumi about burglaries. When the Detective Boys hear his warning, they decide to investigate the burglaries themselves.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: 円谷光彦の探偵ノート2

REGULAR.description:
Sako Manabu, a man with bloody clothes, arrives at the Mori Detective Agency. After a series of unfortunate events, yesterday Sako went out to drown his sorrows, but he can`t remember what happened. When he woke up, his glasses were broken and his clothes were covered with blood. He only had a bump on his head, so he realized the blood belonged to someone else. Concerned that he might have done something terrible, he sought help. Though they initially believe there are no clues, Conan finds hints on Sako`s body...
Source: crunchyroll

Ran, Kogoro, and Sonoko arrive at a popular restaurant. Conan and Professor Agasa join them inside after showing up late, where they are greeted by Nanjo, president of Suzuki Security, in disguise. He has been receiving threats since he provoked the thieves who stole a safe the other day, and is feeling constrained by the bodyguards assigned to him. Later, Nanjo steps away to visit the restroom. Conan realizes the professor has been in the restroom for a long time, and when he goes to check on him...!
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Hagiwara Chihaya, Goddess of the Wind (Part 1)
風の女神・萩原千速 (前編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, Kogoro, Sonoko, and the professor visit a popular restaurant. The professor runs into Nanjo, who asks to swap places with him, and he is mistakenly kidnapped by a couple who were planning to kidnap Nanjo. While pursuing the culprits, Conan is rescued by Kanagawa police officer Hagiwara Chihaya. They pursue the yellow getaway vehicle on Chihaya`s motorbike, but the detective badge they had been relying on is disposed of. The professor still has in his possession a listening device, and they use the sound heard through it alone to continue their pursuit...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Hagiwara Chihaya, Goddess of the Wind (Part 2)
風の女神・萩原千速 (後編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Kogoro, and Ran visit the home of client Nemoto Eriko. Three months ago, Eriko lost her husband Nemoto Yutaka in a traffic accident. While going through his things, she found 20 million yen in the back of the closet. Believing it could be dirty money, Eriko hired Kogoro to determine where the money came from. Kogoro considers the possibilities of savings or lottery winnings but eventually begins investigating armed robberies that took place recently. They narrow down the list of possible cases and visit the victims.
Source: crunchyroll

Conan and Kogoro discover the body of Tsukuba Corporation president Tsukuba. He died after falling from the roof of a building, and a mysterious message was inside his pocket. When they visit his office to gather information, the employees respond to the message`s words "third time`s the charm". Tsukuba was attacked twice over the span of several days. Just as the police decide to investigate the death as a successful attack by the culprit, Tsukuba`s aunt shows up and says she received a call suggesting it might be a suicide. The police begin investigating the death as both a murder and suicide, but...
Source: crunchyroll

Conan, Ran, and Sonoko visit the exhibition of up-and-coming artist Bekobe Motoko. Motoko has attracted international attention with her avant-garde works that combine the traditional akabeko with modern art. While viewing the exhibition, they hear a scream. They rush to the source, where they find Motoko strangled to death. In the body`s left hand is an akabeko, and her right hand is pointing at a dying message that says "fuku"...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: Akabeko to Sannin no Fuku Otoko
The Akabeko and the Three Lucky Men
Seishun Shousetsu ni Tsumi no Nioi
The Teen Novel That Smells Like Guilt

REGULAR.description:
While playing in the park, Conan and the Detective Boys find a man`s body in the bushes. According to the police, the man is Takamatsu Jiro, who worked in a nearby building as a moneylender, leading them to believe the murder may have been an armed robbery or related to money troubles. The blood on the rock used to kill him suggests the culprit is covered in blood. The children, who were in the park the whole time, didn`t see anyone suspicious, and the trail of bloody footprints they find ends abruptly.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The True Culprit Is on the Run

REGULAR.description:
Conan, Ran, and Sonoko visit the Robanov imperial treasures exhibit. The highlight of the exhibition is a tiara set with the world`s largest garnet passed down from queen to queen known as the Queen`s Bang. Because Kaito Kid has declared his intent to steal the tiara, a long line has formed at the exhibition. They find Amuro and Azusa in line, and they decide to wait in line together. While waiting, at Azusa`s suggestion, Amuro performs a magic trick to kill time, but...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: キッドVS安室 王妃の前髪[クイーンズ・バング] (前編)

REGULAR.description:
The Queen`s Bang tiara, centerpiece of the Robanov imperial treasures exhibit, is stolen by Kaito Kid! The exhibition hall is suddenly enveloped in white smoke, and by the time it has cleared, the tiara inside the case has vanished. Because a gas mask would ruin his disguise, it`s unlikely Kaito Kid was wearing one. The suspects are narrowed down to Amuro, Azusa, and Kazami, who were standing near the tiara without masks, so Conan decides to investigate.
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: キッドVS安室 王妃の前髪[クイーンズ・バング] (後編)

REGULAR.description:
Conan and Kogoro visit the home of real estate company manager Sanada on a job. However, Sanada says he no longer needs his help and offers him a cancellation fee. Sanada`s eagerness for them to leave leads Kogoro to question him, and Sanada begins explaining that he never intended to kill anyone. Three days earlier, Sanada`s real estate office was visited by a man named Inumaru. Blackmailed over wrongdoings he never committed, Sanada asked his friend Kawakatsu for advice, but then something happened.
Source: crunchyroll

Mitsuhiko and Genta enjoy playing a trading card game against each other at a table set up in a used bookstore. Conan, Ayumi, Haibara, and Professor Agasa are with them. TCG tournament regulars Nitta, Masaki, Zaizen, and Kuno show up. As usual, Zaizen heads to the bathroom before the game. He instructs Kuno to watch his valuable rare cards, so Nitta as well as Conan and his friends move away from the table. Suddenly, the store enters a state of chaos...
Source: crunchyroll

titles.title: The Secret Hidden by the Cards
